The 16th edition of the Daily Trust Dialogue will hold tomorrow, January 17, 2019, at 10 am in Abuja. The event themed “Youth and Democracy: The Nigerian Challenge” would be held at the NAF Conference Centre and Suite, along Ahmadu Bello Way, Kado, Abuja. The event is open to members of the public. The Emir of Gombe, Alhaji Abubakar Shehu-Abubakar III would serve as the special guest of honour, while Professor Jibrin Ibrahim, Senior Fellow at the Centre for Democracy and Development (CDD), will chair the occasion. Guest speakers at the dialogue are Senator Yusuf Datti Baba-Ahmed, former presidential aspirant; Mrs Maryam Uwais, Special Adviser to the President on Social Protection Plan; and Mr Samson Itodo, Coordinator, Not Too Young to Run. The annual dialogue would be streamed live on the Daily Trust TV. Daily Trust dialogue holds Thursday Daily Trust African of the Year award dinner holds tonight Daily Trust Women Entrepreneurs summit & Exhibition holds tomorrow